^-{ ^*BDeal of the Week 372 - October 27, 2003^*N
 ^*BBy Fred Gitelman^*N }
^-
I am told that there are approximately 100 million people in the world who know how to play bridge. This week's deal was played by one of my very favorite bridge players, ^*BBénédicte Cronier^*N of France. Béné played this week's deal on ^*BBridge Base Online^*N (^*BBBO^*N), the ^*B100% free^*N online bridge service that was developed by my company.

The fact that Béné is a world class bridge player who frequently plays on ^*BBBO^*N is not what makes her special - there are ^*Bmany^*N other great champions who have made ^*BBBO^*N into their online home for bridge. What makes Béné special is Béné herself - she is one of the most charming, enthusiastic, and fun bridge players I have ever met.

Béné cares deeply about the future of our game and I am fortunate that she has recognized the potential that ^*BBBO^*N offers in terms of helping to make bridge more popular. Béné was one of the main driving forces behind organizing our recent ^*Blive^*N online vugraph broadcasts of the ^*B2003 World Youth Team Championships^*N. She was also one of the key people in terms of arranging for our upcoming vugraph coverage of the ^*B2003 World Bridge Championships^*N.

These championships will take place in Monte Carlo from November 2 to 15. Every session will be covered ^*Blive^*N on ^*BBBO^*N and experts from around the world will be on hand to provide the audience with commentary and analysis in several languages. I am grateful to both Béné and her friend, ^*BHervé Lustman^*N, for making it possible for ^*BBBO^*N to cover this year's World Championships.

